input_str: As President Trump has tweeted, Germany has a significant trade surplus with the United States. In 2016, Germany sold $67 billion more in goods and services to the United States than it bought. The U.S. administration, from the president on down, has been very critical of Germany’s exporting success. In two forthcoming government reports, one on surpluses and one on steel exports, Germany is expected to be identified as a country whose exports are problematic
